records.addlTxt:
9:33 A.M.  Defendant present in court with Atty Barb Privat.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Court recites agreement, will plea to the charge without enhancer.  DA concurs.  Atty Privat concurs.  Defendant concurs.  

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.  (If felony) Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions.

Defendant enters a plea of GUILTY.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty.  Court strikes the enhancer.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  DA confirms compliance with victim witness rights.  Sentencing statement by DA.  Sentencing statement by Atty Privat.  Statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:  SWD, and places the defendant on probation for a period of 30 months.

CONDITIONS:

50 days county jail.  Court has no objection to out of county transfer.  Huber.  Sentence is to commence within 60 days.
Defendant is to re-pay the buy-money of $250.00
Court costs
Defendant is to abide by all rules and recommendations of the supervising agent.
Defendant is to complete a High School diplomacy or equivalency

Court grants the defendant sentence credit of 4 days
